title: [The Skeptic]
description: Overhead, spiderwebs cling to the ceiling, which is hung with two tarnished, three-piece chandeliers.  Several platinum, free-standing racks take up the center of the wagon's space, their metal as shiny and bright as the vividness of the carmine flooring they stand on.  On every side, the walls of the wagon appear old and unkempt, including a door framed by a gooey black substance.

Overhead, spiderwebs cling to the ceiling, which is hung with two tarnished, three-piece chandeliers.  Several platinum, free-standing racks and a hazelnut armoire take up the main of the wagon's space, their metal as shiny and bright as the vividness of the carmine flooring they stand on.  Save for the area directly around an oval archway, the walls and a door, which is framed by a gooey black substance, appear old and unkempt.
